AMI is a ready-to-use template that contains everything needed to launch an EC2 instance.

Component	                      Description
Operating System	e.g.,         Amazon Linux 2, Ubuntu, Windows
Installed Software	e.g.,       httpd, MySQL, Node.js
Configurations	                All settings and configurations pre-applied
Storage Mapping	                EBS volume details

💡 Simple Analogy:
Think of AMI like a Xerox/Photocopy 🖨️

You have one original document (your EC2 instance)
AMI takes a photocopy of it
You can print as many copies as you want from that photocopy
Every copy will be exactly the same as the original
